\f0\b\fs52 \cf2 Balsamic Vinegar Caramelized Onions
\b0\fs44 \
2 yellow onions, julienned\
Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper\
1/4 cup good quality baslamic vinegar\
2 T brown sugar\
1 T fresh thyme, minced\
Extra virgin olive oil\
Heat a saute pan large enough to hold all of the onions with a bit of olive oil over medium heat.\'a0 Add the onions and saute until they just begin to color, tossing frequently.\'a0 Add the balsamic vinegar and brown sugar and stir or toss to combine.\'a0 Cover, reduce the heat, and let cook for about 30-35 minutes, or until the onions have cooked down and caramelized deeply.\'a0 Add the thyme and toss to combine.\'a0 Serve.\'a0\
